McMahon's lawyer said he would appeal to the guilty ruling.

### Two Chinese citizens are convicted

There are two other Chinese citizens who lived in the United States in this case, namely Zheng Cong Conying and Zhu Yong (transliteration, zhuyong) who provided preliminary information to him in 2016 and provided preliminary information.

![](Images/dwzh/2023-06-21T02-08-00Z/63466815_401.jpg)China has been accused of expanding monitoring and coercion to overseas through the "fox hunting operation" (schematic diagram).

Prosecutor said that the victim of the case Xu Jin served as a municipal official of Wuhan before moving the United States, and China accused him of collecting bribes with his wife Liu Fang. Xu Jin's husband and wife denied corruption and claimed to be the target of attack because of conflict with the CCP's power structure.

